<i>verb</i>: 삭다 [삭따] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>삭다 [삭따]</dt><br>
<dd>1. decay; wear thin; molder</dd><br>
<dd>오래되어 썩거나 약하게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For something to rot or become weak because it is old.</dd><br>
<dd>2. become watery; become sloppy</dd><br>
<dd>걸쭉한 것이 묽어지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For something thick to become washy.</dd><br>
<dd>3. ferment; develop flavor</dd><br>
<dd>김치나 젓갈 등의 음식물이 발효되어 맛이 알맞게 되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For food such as gimchi/kimchi, salted fish, etc., to come to taste good after undergoing fermentation.</dd><br>
<dd>4. be digested; be assimilated</dd><br>
<dd>음식물이 소화되다.</dd><br>
<dd>For food to digest.</dd><br>
<dd>5. be appeased; be alleviated; melt away</dd><br>
<dd>긴장이나 화가 풀리다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's tension or anger to be allayed.</dd><br>
<dd>6. die out; go out</dd><br>
<dd>불이 사그라져 재가 되거나 없어지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For fire to be reduced to ashes or be extinguished.</dd><br>
<dd>7. fade; lose vigor</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 얼굴이나 몸이 생기를 잃다.</dd><br>
<dd>For someone's face or body to lose vitality.</dd><br>
<dd>8. decrease</dd><br>
<dd>기침이나 가래 등이 멎거나 가라앉다.</dd><br>
<dd>For coughing, phlegm, etc., to stop or be relieved.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>